<subSubSection id="2F93CAB63EDD1A3E7791804ED84B190C" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="BB2BB4CFA64FBF4BCE9D90D05798D819" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Macroscopic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB14D3AEF3C0F6C4042B510361EBF037" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Cap 2.5-7.5 cm, convex to irregularly gibbous, sometimes broadly umbonate, with incurved later straight, opaque margin, occasionally appendiculate, dry and dull, unicolored mainly sepia, sometimes with light grayish adpressed covering. Lamellae almost free to emarginate gray (olive) brown, edge entire, slightly tomentose, number of lamellae {L} 45-58. Stem whitish pale fibrillose, sordid gray-brown, often more or less buried in sand with a sand bulb around the base, cortina pale. Context initially fairly thick, with cavity, firm watery grayish in pileus, pale brownish in stipe to near buff, towards base dark, sordid brown. Smell weakly and indistinctly raphanoid. Taste similar, mild. Spore deposit color not recorded.</paragraph>
<caption id="F07844B5FF6EC97B663B57A029990D11" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.79.63363.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/533400" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
<paragraph id="0119CD7638EB7E34580BD16742730BE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="F0F04A5C75A7E413BC444D244E872AF2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Figure 9.</emphasis>
