<subSubSection id="33F5663C45AF2F594921AEA9A3A97EB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="718702C72C1FE883B60C2CF491D513C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C6B69F3565BBE74639CC981AEFD1286" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Known from a few collections from three localities in southwestern Greenland. 
<taxonomicName id="D03B703A44DA6EBB70C530A58C2F3088" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Salicaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. colvinii" order="Salicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="colvinii">
<emphasis id="E5D6BD66198173E07C8F5612C92AD959" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. colvinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="19394CC6085C709FCFF428B872A86716" author="Peck, CH" journalOrPublisher="North American Fungi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B39" refString="Peck, CH, 1875. Report of the Botanist (1874) Annual Report on the New York State Museum of Natural History 28: 31-88." title="Report of the Botanist (1874) Annual Report on the New York State Museum of Natural History 28: 31 - 88." year="1875">Peck (1875</bibRefCitation>
; effectively published 1876) from West Albany in North America. He found it in drifting sand in West Albany near Albany, N.Y. State. Later 
<bibRefCitation id="0FE9B2F7221325AD44913A5B65A0B1EC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.58545" author="Kauffman, CH" journalOrPublisher="Wynkoop Hallenbeck Crawford Co., Lansing" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B29" refString="Kauffman, CH, 1918. The Agaricaceae of Michigan. Wynkoop Hallenbeck Crawford Co., Lansing, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.58545" title="The Agaricaceae of Michigan." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.58545" year="1918">Kauffman (1918)</bibRefCitation>
reported this or a very similar species from New Richmond in Michigan, as did 
<bibRefCitation id="AAB24826D9AC20FDD3054250DCC31F06" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00131724609339958" author="Ritchie, D" journalOrPublisher="Castanea" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="125 - 127" refId="B41" refString="Ritchie, D, 1946. Hebeloma colvini, a rare mushroom from a sandy beach. Castanea 11: 125 - 127, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00131724609339958" title="Hebeloma colvini, a rare mushroom from a sandy beach." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00131724609339958" volume="11" year="1946">Ritchie (1946)</bibRefCitation>
from Lewes, Delaware Bay. Neither of these two collections has been examined as part of this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB7F5F1288C6A9716B4FB652E5F30ACD" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="B18A4E6ACF2D92DAF43CD5372CD721E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Habitat and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B08262CC652079FA83AF6FDB553F9EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Five collections, all with 
<taxonomicName id="88EC92DF608EE5D1284E37D053B4C9CC" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Salix glauca" order="Salicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis id="C327C8274AB6CB49F18719EDFE18C136" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Salix glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pure sand along a river. In one of the localities, Sandflugtsdalen (&quot;valley of driftsand&quot;) at Kangerlussuaq, it was very common and scattered over a large area. The sand is mineral-rich due to mixing with loess.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="575B719819760380D31878C88586DCE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="notes">
<paragraph id="972C1C91B98740758661AD76C5905D45" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D9434C6CF7131009BB48C3E55F4C7BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="287F30B7A932C9E1CA1A0E336E79A89E" authorityName="Sacc.; Syll. fung. (Abellini) 5: 805" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Peck" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma colvinii" order="Ostropales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="colvinii">
<emphasis id="6F6FABD814724932973717F44B625F2D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hebeloma colvinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="4F3AD701441CF49B845A46003F886773" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Agaricaceae" genus="Agaricus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Agaricus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="913EBD6D790EF0A7D7F7E9F15FBAE63F" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma colvini" order="Ostropales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="colvini">Hebeloma colvini</taxonomicName>
&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="1903913D3D87F4EA8AB906D9CAE7F007" author="Peck, CH" journalOrPublisher="North American Fungi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B39" refString="Peck, CH, 1875. Report of the Botanist (1874) Annual Report on the New York State Museum of Natural History 28: 31-88." title="Report of the Botanist (1874) Annual Report on the New York State Museum of Natural History 28: 31 - 88." year="1875">Peck 1875</bibRefCitation>
). The name is currently not in use, e.g. there are no records on Mushroom Observer (https://mushroomobserver.org/, accessed 23 Sept 2020) and while Mycoportal (https://mycoportal.org/portal/collections/list.php, accessed 2 Dec 2020) has 63 records, the most recent is from 1972. The identification of the Greenland collections is supported by unpublished studies of type material. It appears that exposed expanses of sandy soil are the characteristic habitat for the species, which is morphologically similar to a number of species of the difficult group around 
<taxonomicName id="89BDA36040702D8883E65FB73CA41F90" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Salicaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. dunense" order="Salicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="dunense">
<emphasis id="293A05AF48623EF0C6C6F23282DF0A99" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. dunense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1FB1F3E2BE1EBA60112646A3F539B957" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Salicaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. mesophaeum" order="Salicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="mesophaeum">
<emphasis id="5191CCCECC0850A7BBECDE8FFCBEF1F2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. mesophaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="77DA64E6878E86B67409AB1DA2ED9A70" authorityName="Sacc.; Syll. fung. (Abellini) 5: 805" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Peck" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma colvinii" order="Ostropales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="colvinii">
<emphasis id="2A5EFFDC74B1B370C3BC37FE86E2A18C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hebeloma colvinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by its large ellipsoid spores, reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="8275A2739AB479DA3A71FCDA87E53E44" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma psammophilum" order="Ostropales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="psammophilum">
<emphasis id="713C3EFDC637C090D61DDDD4A9F79635" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hebeloma psammophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is currently known only from western Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="C8C71BC5BFEBB3D8D4278FB619421FCC" author="Beker, HJ" journalOrPublisher="Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B4" refString="Beker, HJ, Eberhardt, U, Vesterholt, J, 2016. Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm. Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" title="Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm." year="2016">Beker et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
